 Also note that for evaluating the retrieval, we always skip the 30 abstention instances. This is because these instances generally refer to non-existing events and do not have a ground truth answer location.
 
+When interpreting retrieval metrics, note that `recall_all@k` is an all-or-nothing metric: every labeled evidence item must appear in the top `k` results. Therefore, if a question has more than 5 labeled evidence sessions, its session-level `recall_all@5` must be 0 even for the best possible ranking. The cleaned `longmemeval_s_cleaned.json` and `longmemeval_m_cleaned.json` files have the same label-count distribution: 3 questions have more than 5 evidence sessions (`gpt4_a1b77f9c`, `gpt4_7abb270c`, `a3838d2b`), so their session-level `recall_all@5` is necessarily 0; 6 questions have more than 5 labeled evidence turns (`gpt4_a56e767c`, `gpt4_7fce9456`, `gpt4_31ff4165`, `gpt4_a1b77f9c`, `gpt4_7abb270c`, `a3838d2b`), so their turn-level `recall_all@5` is necessarily 0. Use `recall_any@5`, `ndcg_any@5`, or `recall_all@30/@50` alongside `recall_all@5` when analyzing multi-label questions.
+
